---

{# ── FOUR ENGAGEMENTS (router) — dc-card hub-card r-2. (H2: Four engagements. Pick the one that fits.) ── #}
<section class="sec reveal" id="bookkeeping-engagements">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Bookkeeping services</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="max-width:26ch;margin-bottom:10px;">Four engagements. Pick the one that fits.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 32px;max-width:66ch;">Most owners aren&rsquo;t sure which engagement they need &mdash; the diagnostic call sorts that. But here is how each is shaped, what it costs, and when it&rsquo;s the right fit. Canonical price ranges shown; your exact fixed fee follows the call.</p>
    <div class="r-2">
      {%- for e in engagements %}
      <article class="dc-card hub-card"><span class="eyebrow">{{ e.area | safe }}</span><h3>{{ e.name | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:15px;margin:6px 0 12px;">{{ e.body | safe }}</p><p class="prose" style="font-size:13.5px;margin:0 0 4px;color:var(--color-ink-mute);"><strong style="color:var(--color-ink);">For:</strong> {{ e.forWho | safe }} &middot; {{ e.cadence | safe }}</p><p class="mono" style="font-size:12px;color:var(--color-ink-mute);margin:0 0 10px;"><strong style="color:var(--color-ink);">{{ e.fee | safe }}</strong></p><a class="hub-card__go" href="{{ e.href }}">{{ e.cta | safe }} <svg width="15" height="15" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M4 12h15M13 6l6 6-6 6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></a></article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── MATCH YOUR SITUATION (decision matrix → vs-table, sand). (H2: Match your situation to the right engagement.) ── #}
<section class="sec reveal" id="bookkeeping-routing" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Which engagement</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="max-width:28ch;margin-bottom:10px;">Match your situation to the right engagement.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 30px;max-width:64ch;">If you&rsquo;re not sure, the diagnostic sorts it. But most starting points fall into one of these patterns.</p>
    <table class="cmp">
      <caption class="sr-only">Which bookkeeping engagement to start with, by the current state of your books, and what follows.</caption>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th scope="col">If you&hellip;</th>
          <th scope="col" class="us">{{ routing.cols[0] | safe }}</th>
          <th scope="col">{{ routing.cols[1] | safe }}</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {%- for row in routing.rows %}
        <tr>
          <th scope="row" data-col="If you…">{{ row.dim | safe }}</th>
          <td class="us" data-col="{{ routing.cols[0] | striptags }}"><strong>{{ row.start | safe }}</strong></td>
          <td data-col="{{ routing.cols[1] | striptags }}">{{ row.then | safe }}</td>
        </tr>
        {%- endfor %}
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── OPERATOR ACCOUNTABILITY, PLATFORM STANDARDS — process-grid (6 steps). (H2: Operator accountability, platform standards.) ── #}
<section class="sec reveal" id="bookkeeping-standards">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Why TechBrot bookkeeping</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">Operator accountability, platform standards.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 30px;max-width:64ch;">Bookkeeping is delivered by independent local practices &mdash; not by anonymous offshore teams or rotating remote subscriptions.</p>
    <div class="process-grid">
      {%- for s in standards %}
      <div class="process-step">
        <span class="process-step__n">0{{ loop.index }}</span>
        <h3>{{ s.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p>{{ s.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── INDUSTRIES — dc-card hub-card r-3 (sand). (H2: Bookkeeping that understands your industry.) ── #}
<section class="sec reveal" id="bookkeeping-industries" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Industries served</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="max-width:26ch;margin-bottom:10px;">Bookkeeping that understands your industry.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 30px;max-width:64ch;">Bookkeeping done well requires understanding how the business actually runs. Our operators bring vertical depth across the industries we serve most.</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for ind in industries %}
      <a class="dc-card hub-card" href="{{ ind.href }}"><h3>{{ ind.label | safe }}</h3></a>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── A NAMED, CREDENTIALED LOCAL OPERATOR — prose + trust-row (white). (H2: A named, credentialed local operator.) ── #}
<section class="sec reveal" id="bookkeeping-operator">
  <div class="ct read">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Who performs the work</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:18px;">A named, credentialed local operator.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Every TechBrot bookkeeping engagement is delivered by a vetted local operator &mdash; an independent accounting practice running under TechBrot&rsquo;s brand, standards, and infrastructure. You know who is closing your books, how to reach them, and what credentials they hold. Platform-level quality review backs every engagement, and continuity is guaranteed if the relationship ever needs to transition.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row">
      {%- for r in operator %}
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">{{ r.label | safe }}</p><p class="trust-row__label">{{ r.detail | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- if not loop.last %}<div class="trust-row__divider"></div>{%- endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── BOOKKEEPING IS OFTEN PART OF A LARGER ENGAGEMENT — dc-card hub-card r-2 (sand). (H2: Bookkeeping is often part of a larger engagement.) ── #}
<section class="sec reveal" id="bookkeeping-adjacent" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Adjacent services</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="max-width:30ch;margin-bottom:28px;">Bookkeeping is often part of a larger engagement.</h2>
    <div class="r-2">
      {%- for n in adjacent %}
      <a class="dc-card hub-card" href="{{ n.href }}"><h3>{{ n.name | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:15px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ n.body | safe }}</p><span class="hub-card__go">{{ n.name | safe }} <svg width="15" height="15" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M4 12h15M13 6l6 6-6 6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></span></a>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <p class="prose" style="margin-top:24px;font-size:14px;color:var(--color-ink-mute);"><a href="/accounting/bookkeeping/faq/">See all bookkeeping FAQs <span aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span></a></p>
  </div>
</section>
